348YRR1X12ZWWYWAIVQ0C8LFI46Z0J.title: Personal Spending in the month of March - DIARY 3(~ 5 minutes)
348YRR1X12ZWWYWAIVQ0C8LFI46Z0J.description: The purpose of this study is to examine people's spending over the course of a month in their lives. In this study we will ask you to tell us about your spending plans for the month of March. We will also ask you questions about your personal situation (e.g., income), your personality and attitudes, and about strategies you use to help you achieve your spending plans.    This study includes an intake survey (~10 minutes) and we will also ask for your permission to contact you for 10 diary surveys throughout the course of the month (~5 minutes each), as well as a final diary report at the end of the month (~5 minutes).  For the intake survey, you will earn US $0.50. For each of the 10 diary reports, you will earn US $0.50 per report (10 x $0.50 = $5.00). For the final report, you will earn US $1.00. The final diary report will be sent on March 31st. Thus, you can earn up to US $6.50 in this study.  Your participation as well as your responses will be strictly confidential, only the researchers will have access to the data (see a list of people who are involved with this study below). At the end of the study, we will destroy all information that was used to contact you for the diary survey and compensation (i.e., MTurk worker identification numbers).   People involved in this study: Johanna Peetz (faculty member), Mariya Davydenko (PhD student). This study has received clearance by the Carleton University Research Ethics Board - B (# 111530).

3V6FYJLHFQQERUH1ZAU5ZOQO96D05N.description: The purpose of this survey is to find potential participants that 1) would be interested in participating in a three-week long online study on effective goal-setting (more details about the study will follow) and 2) meet the required criteria to participate in said study. For this short screening survey, we would like you to answer some questions about your current life situation. If you meet the required criteria for participation in the main study, then we will also ask you to set several career-related goals after which you will answer some questions about them. We will determine whether you meet the required criteria with the first four questions in the survey. If the required criteria are met, you will be able to proceed with the survey. If these criteria are not met after the first four questions, the survey will automatically end and you will not be compensated. Once you submit the survey, we will evaluate your responses. We will contact you in a few days if you are qualified to take part in the main study.

39RCRL1COGSMAOD4JUVNQWQVHPZ7SK.description: Arabs have the second highest prevalence of chronic low back pain worldwide. Yet, we do not know how widespread low back pain is among Arabs living in the United States.   If you are an Arab-American or an Arab who lives in the United States, and you have low back pain, we are inviting you to complete a short screener (< 2 minutes). You will be answering questions about your ethnic background and your condition. Your participation is voluntary and will help inform our understanding of low back pain among Arab-Americans and Arabs living in the United States.   Your responses will be checked by the research team before approving your HIT. So, kindly make sure that you answer the questions the best you can. If your HIT is approved you will receive $0.30 as payment. Only those matching the eligibility criteria will be invited to complete the full-length survey for an additional payment. If you do not qualify for the survey, please return the HIT. To participate click the link below:

See the section titled “Session 2 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

31ZOAI992ICKXOHM6Y0L1V7OC0WTLR.description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 3 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

3YJAOW5N8OV96O7STBBA4IFQEEGNSX.description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 3 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.
